(
<figureCitation id="1370A7EAFFF8FFB2FF3C331DFE97FC7D" box="[160,279,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1219,1243]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,417,1195]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,417,1195]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A. Paracineta livadiana (Mereschkowsky, 1881) attached on nematode host (arrow indicating ciliate), B. Magnified view of Paracineta livadiana, C. Loricophrya bosporica Sergeeva &amp; Dovgal, 2016 attached on nematode host (arrow indicating ciliate), D. Magnified view of Loricophrya bosporica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571803/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C351E8E4FFF8FFB2FF0B33D4FBD5FBA5" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BF4BB6FFFF8FFB2FF0B33D4FDF5FC11" blockId="2.[151,1437,942,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FF0B33D4FE03FC34" bold="true" box="[151,387,942,968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Material examined:</emphasis>
One individual found as epibiont on nematode host belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FB4933D5FAD8FC35" box="[1237,1368,943,969]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Desmodora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FB4933D5FAD8FC35" box="[1237,1368,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Desmodora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<quantity id="4CB3168AFFF8FFB2FF0B33A9FF5EFC11" box="[151,222,979,1005]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.02" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" unit="m" value="202.0">202 m</quantity>
depth of Arabian Sea, Indian Ocean
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF4BB6FFFF8FFB2FF5B338CFBD5FBA5" blockId="2.[151,1437,942,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FF5B338CFE20FBEC" bold="true" box="[199,416,1014,1040]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Brief Description:</emphasis>
Marine suctorian ciliate with a rounded body, almost covered with a stylotheca. The tentacles are arranged at apical body surface. Stylotheca with stem-like pseudostyle that does not widen until it transitions into the widened part of the stylotheca. The macronucleus is ellipsoidal, central.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C351E8E4FFF8FFB2FF5B3419FD06FB39" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF4BB6FFFF8FFB2FF5B3419FD06FB39" blockId="2.[151,1437,942,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FF5B3419FD10FB80" bold="true" box="[199,656,1122,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Measurements from present specimen</emphasis>
(in µm, based on one individual): Stylotheca length 32; lorica width 20; body length 21; body width 13; pseudostyle length 7; pseudostyle diameter 3; macronucleus length 5; macronucleus width 4; length of the tentacles 4–8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C351E8E4FFF8FFB2FF5B34B5FBD3F9AD" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF4BB6FFFF8FFB2FF5B34B5FEE0F9D1" blockId="2.[151,1437,942,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FF5B34B5FEB4FB15" bold="true" box="[199,308,1231,1257]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Remarks</emphasis>
: This is a marine or brackish-water species, that can settle on the surface of the body of invertebrates and other substrates. Mereschkowsky (1881) described this species as epibiont on hydroids 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FB013489FAB5FAF1" box="[1181,1333,1267,1293]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sertulariidae" genus="Sertularia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FB013489FA8FFAF1" box="[1181,1295,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Sertularia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
from the Black Sea near Livadia (Yalta). The species was reported attached on hydroids 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FBB0356DFF4FFAA9" authority="McCrady, 1859" authorityName="McCrady" authorityYear="1859" class="Hydrozoa" family="Campanulariidae" genus="Obelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="commissuralis">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FBB0356DFAA4FACD" box="[1068,1316,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Obelia commissuralis</emphasis>
McCrady, 1859
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FE993541FDE3FAA9" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[261,611,1338,1365]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Campanulariidae" genus="Obelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="geniculata">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FE993541FE1DFAA9" box="[261,413,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">O. geniculata</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
from Woods Hole, 
<collectingCountry id="F35CFBFFFFF8FFB2FCA23541FCF4FAA9" box="[830,884,1339,1365]" name="United States of America" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAC69EFFF8FFB2FC1F3541FC7EFAA9" author="Root, F. M." box="[899,1022,1339,1365]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" pagination="77 - 81" refId="ref3932" refString="Root, F. M. (1922) A new suctorian from Woods Hole. Transactions of the American Microscopical Society, 41 (2), 77 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3221897" type="journal article" year="1922">Root 1922</bibRefCitation>
). This species was found from Mediterranean Sea (
<collectingRegion id="498F758DFFF8FFB2FEA13525FE29FA85" box="[317,425,1375,1401]" country="Egypt" name="Bur Sa'id" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Port Said</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F35CFBFFFFF8FFB2FE293525FE7AFA85" box="[437,506,1375,1401]" name="Egypt" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Egypt</collectingCountry>
) and at the Atlantic coast of the 
<collectingCountry id="F35CFBFFFFF8FFB2FCF83525FC1AFA85" box="[868,922,1375,1401]" name="United States of America" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAC69EFFF8FFB2FC363525FBC2FA85" author="Dovgal, I. V." box="[938,1090,1375,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 267" refId="ref3494" refString="Dovgal, I. V. (2013) Ciliates - Ciliophora. Issue 1. Class Suctorea. In: Fauna of Ukraine vol. 36. Naukova dumka, Kiev, pp. 1 - 267. [in Russian with English summary]" type="book chapter" year="2013">Dovgal 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The species was registered in the Black Sea on algae 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FE0535F9FDC7FA61" box="[409,583,1411,1437]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FE0535F9FDA0FA61" box="[409,544,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Cladophora</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
near Sevastopol and on 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FCCA35F9FB83FA61" box="[854,1027,1411,1437]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FCCA35F9FC5DFA61" box="[854,989,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Cladophora</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and crab 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FBF235F9FEDAFA3D" authority="(Fabricius, 1787)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" class="Malacostraca" family="Grapsidae" genus="Pachygrapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FBF235F9FA1CFA60" box="[1134,1436,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Pachygrapsus marmoratus</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1787)
</taxonomicName>
from the coast of the Karadag Natural Reserve (Crimea) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAC69EFFF8FFB2FC6635DDFB14FA3D" author="Dovgal, I. V." box="[1018,1172,1447,1473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 267" refId="ref3494" refString="Dovgal, I. V. (2013) Ciliates - Ciliophora. Issue 1. Class Suctorea. In: Fauna of Ukraine vol. 36. Naukova dumka, Kiev, pp. 1 - 267. [in Russian with English summary]" type="book chapter" year="2013">Dovgal 2013</bibRefCitation>
). It was observed from harpacticoid copepods 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FE3E35B1FCEAFA19" authority="(Willey, 1935)" baseAuthorityName="Willey" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[418,874,1482,1509]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Miraciidae" genus="Amphiascella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Harpacticoida" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subdebilis">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FE3E35B1FD37FA19" box="[418,695,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Amphiascella subdebilis</emphasis>
(Willey, 1935)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FCE635B1FAABFA19" authority="Por, 1959" authorityName="Por" authorityYear="1959" box="[890,1323,1482,1509]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Miraciidae" genus="Haloschizopera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Harpacticoida" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontarchis">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FCE635B1FB2DFA19" box="[890,1197,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Haloschizopera pontarchis</emphasis>
Por, 1959
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FAA635B1FEFBF9F5" authority="Scott, 1896" authorityName="Scott" authorityYear="1896" class="Hexanauplia" family="Cletodidae" genus="Cletodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Harpacticoida" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuipes">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FAA635B1FF74F9F4" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Cletodes tenuipes</emphasis>
Scott, 1896
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4BC0ECFFF8FFB2FE2D3595FCECF9F5" authority="Sars, 1909" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1909" box="[433,876,1519,1545]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Cletodidae" genus="Enhydrosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Harpacticoida" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longifurcatum">
<emphasis id="B93F677DFFF8FFB2FE2D3595FD70F9F5" box="[433,752,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Enhydrosoma longifurcatum</emphasis>
Sars, 
<quantity id="4CB3168AFFF8FFB2FCA83595FCECF9F5" box="[820,876,1519,1545]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.84886" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" unit="in" value="1909.0">1909</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in the hypoxic zone of the Black Sea by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDAC69EFFF8FFB2FAAA3595FEDBF9D1" author="Sergeeva, N. G. &amp; Dovgal, I." pageId="2" pageNumber="494" pagination="49 - 54" refId="ref4099" refString="Sergeeva, N. G. &amp; Dovgal, I. (2014) First finding of epibiont peritrich and suctorian ciliates (Ciliophora) on oligochaetes and harpacticoid copepods from the deep-water hypoxic / anoxic conditions of the Black Sea. Ecologica Montenegrina, 1, 49 - 54. https: // doi. org / 10.37828 / em. 2014.1.7" type="journal article" year="2014">Sergeeva &amp; Dovgal (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF4BB6FFFF8FFB2FF5B364DFBD3F9AD" blockId="2.[151,1437,942,1617]" box="[199,1107,1591,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">This is the first report of this species from the Arabian Sea and the Indian Ocean.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
